				\begin{document}$$N_s$$\end{document} sources on a uniform grid of size Ng3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$N_g^3$$\end{document}, and requiring that each grid cell has at least one ray from each source passing through it, the number of rays required is Ns×6×Ng2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
