				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$z\gtrsim 10$$\end{document} to the fluctuating Lyman-α\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\alpha $$\end{document} opacity of the z∼5.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$z\sim 5.5$$\end{document} IGM; (3) reveal the thermal history of cosmic gas through the imprint left by hydrogen and helium reionization heating on the power spectrum of the Lyman-α\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
